The reset command accepts one or two args, distinguished by dots. Two args, first without dot, second with dot → link-style edge reset (marker, spec). Two args, both with dots → spec-spec edge reset (reviewed spec, source spec). One arg → orphan removal (spec if dotted, marker otherwise). Missing arguments return a usage error showing all forms. On link-style success: "Resolved: FROM → TO. Baseline updated." On spec-spec success: "Resolved edge: X reviewed against Y." On orphan success: "Removed deleted spec/marker X from state.xml." On error returns the error message. All forms exit 0 on success, 1 on error. See principles.friction.